Interface Dna

All Superinterfaces:
BioPAXElement, Cloneable, Controller, Entity, Level3Element, Named, NucleicAcid, Observable, PhysicalEntity, SequenceEntity, Serializable, SimplePhysicalEntity, XReferrable
All Known Implementing Classes:
DnaImpl
public interface Dna extends NucleicAcid
Definition: A physical entity consisting of a sequence of deoxyribonucleotide monophosphates; a deoxyribonucleic acid. Usage: DNA should be used for pools of individual DNA molecules. For describing subregions on those molecules use DNARegion. Examples: a chromosome, a plasmid. A specific example is chromosome 7 of Homo sapiens.
